      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) features the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, delivering linear power through individual throttle bodies and optimized by dual-VANOS variable valve timing. Paired with a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory M Variable Differential Lock, the drivetrain remains tight and responsive. The chassis has undergone a preventative rear subframe reinforcement, ensuring structural integrity under high lateral loads. Suspension components retain their factory geometry with refreshed bushings, providing the tactile feedback and turn-in precision this platform is known for. While showing minor signs of use consistent with its age, this M3 is mechanically robust and ready for the apex.",
